body:
Okay @AudriusButkevicius, I'm convinced. It would be a very incomplete feature screaming for all those bells and whistles you described.  I understand why the BEP should not be bloated with stuff that is not sync-specific.

So @calmh your plan is basically a bookmark system within Syncthing's GUI instead of some browser instance, but reusing the discovery mechanism for Dynamic DNS ;-) I could live with that.

@AudriusButkevicius about the certificate, sorry I thought the HTTPS connection used the same certificate as the sync connection because I see no sense in separating them.  To me, the sync protocol and the GUI are just two different endpoints on the same server, so could be identified by the same certificates.  Which would also simplify the trust decision when doing remote GUI access.
